dfischer.utils

Interface LoadtestPluginInterface

  • All Superinterfaces:
    GenericPluginInterface

    public interface LoadtestPluginInterface
extends GenericPluginInterface
    Allows to define fixed configuration settings for load test plug-ins.
    See Also:
    GenericPluginInterface.TYPE_LOADTEST_EXEC, LoadtestPluginContext, LoadtestPluginFixedUserInputField

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int CONSTRUCT_SCOPE_GLOBAL
      The plug-in can be only constructed one time during the load test.
      static int CONSTRUCT_SCOPE_LOOP
      The plug-in can be only constructed per executed loop.
      static int CONSTRUCT_SCOPE_NOT_FIXED
      The construction of the plug-in is not fixed (freely choosable).
      static int CONSTRUCT_SCOPE_USER
      The plug-in can be only constructed per emulated user.
      static int EXEC_ORDER_AFTER
      The plug-in is called after the test/user/loop/URL is processed.
      static int EXEC_ORDER_BEFORE
      The plug-in is called before the test/user/loop/URL is processed.
      static int EXEC_ORDER_NOT_FIXED
      The plug-in can be called before or after the test/user/loop/URL is processed.
      static int EXEC_SCOPE_ALL_URLS
      The plug-in is bound to every (all) URL calls (before or after the URL calls are executed).
      static int EXEC_SCOPE_GLOBAL
      The plug-in can be only called one time during the load test (start or end of test).
      static int EXEC_SCOPE_LOOP
      The plug-in is called per executed loop (start or end of loop).
      static int EXEC_SCOPE_NOT_FIXED
      The call of the plug-in is not fixed (freely choosable).
      static int EXEC_SCOPE_URL
      The plug-in is bound to a specific URL call (before or after URL call).
      static int EXEC_SCOPE_USER
      The plug-in is called per emulated user (create or destroy user).

      • getFixedUserInputFields

        LoadtestPluginFixedUserInputField[] getFixedUserInputFields()
        Returns an array of "fixed User Input Fields", or null if this functionality is not supported or needed for the plug-in configuration at the Web Admin GUI.

        If an array is returned it must have the same size like the method GenericPluginInterface.getInputParameterLabels() returns. Array Elements (input parameter) for which no "User Input Field" should be defined must be set to a value of null.

        Returns:
        an array of "fixed User Input Fields", or null. Some or all array elements can be also null.
        See Also:
        GenericPluginInterface.getInputParameterLabels()
